                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="220360" author="jgmitter" created="Wed, 7 Feb 2018 20:15:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is this work still needed?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="208558" author="adilger" created="Sat, 16 Sep 2017 01:46:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think (most of) the nameless objects in osd-zfs are being fixed as part of ZFS OI Scrub patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/28610&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/28610&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="166232" author="jay" created="Fri, 16 Sep 2016 06:37:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, all dynamically created object with seq number ```FID_SEQ_LOCAL_NAME``` don&apos;t have names.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="166231" author="gerrit" created="Fri, 16 Sep 2016 06:34:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Jinshan Xiong (jinshan.xiong@intel.com) uploaded a new patch: &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/22543&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/22543&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Subject: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8620&quot; title=&quot;Get rid of mystery object &amp;#39;???&amp;lt;object#138&amp;gt;&amp;#39; from the output of zdb&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-8620&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-8620&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; osd-zfs: Create acct object under root directory&lt;br/&gt;
Project: fs/lustre-release&lt;br/&gt;
Branch: master&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: 1&lt;br/&gt;
Commit: c63638f441c5bcf639863cc3fc4d6936148f3692&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="166230" author="adilger" created="Fri, 16 Sep 2016 06:34:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This specific object will become obsolete as soon as the ZFS dnode accounting feature is available for use.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, I think that there may be other ZFS OSD objects that similarly do not have a proper pathname (only a FID), but I don&apos;t have any specific example right now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
